{"title":"Campagnolo Makes Poetic Return to the World Tour Racing with Team Cofidis","link":"https://bikerumor.com/campagnolo-returns-to-the-world-tour-racing-with-team-cofidis/","date":1733428854000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-bike--1536x1024.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis TT bike\" /></p>\n<p>There has been much speculation about Campagnolo this year. The storied Italian component manufacturer was left off cycling’s most prestigious stage after being flicked by French powerhouse Decathlon-AG2R for Shimano in 2024. For the 2025 season, Campagnolo has a seat back at the world tour table with another iconic French outfit — Cofidis.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1801\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-scaled.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis TT\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-297x209.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-1536x1081.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-120x84.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-768x540.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-2048x1441.webp 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(All Images: Campagnolo) </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Campagnolo Returns to the World Tour </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s poetic that another French World Tour team would ring the bells for Campagnolo’s return to the World Tour. The news has many Campagnolo fans breathing a sigh of relief after a few years of watching the brand fall away from professional racing. Now, along with Team Cofidis, Campagnolo looks to add another chapter to its 90-year racing history.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--1536x1024.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-shifter--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"2303\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--1536x2303.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis Chainset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--1536x2303.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--768x1151.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--1024x1536.webp 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--1366x2048.webp 1366w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Chainset--scaled.webp 1707w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Where Has Campy Been?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Campagnolo hasn’t been dormant; on the contrary, they’ve released quite a few products in the past two years. Many of which take a slight step out of their comfort zone, like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/campagnolo-super-record-s-wireless-special-edition-road-bike-groupset-drops-in-price/\">Super Record S</a> and<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/just-in-campagnolo-ekar-gt-gravel-gruppo-actual-weight-is-lighter-than-expected/\"> Ekar GT</a>, to name a few. However, the presence of SRAM and Shimano has grown so exponentially that it seemed challenging for the Vicentine company to compete.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--1536x1024.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-road-bike--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Starting January 1st, 2025, Cofidis and their new LOOK bikes will be outfitted with the newest Campagnolo shifting components and wheels. The agreement will run for the next four years and includes both the men’s and women’s Cofidis squads. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis front of factory\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-front-of-factory--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>LOOK and Campagnolo Combo </strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2025 Cofidis team edition LOOK bikes will be specced with the newest Campagnolo Super Record Wireless groupset. With this, riders will have their pick of cassettes, cranksets, lengths, and everything in between—it’s good to be the pro. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--1536x1024.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis Look Bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Look-Bike--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-1536x1024.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis TT wheels\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-TT-wheels-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Wheels-wise, Cofidis riders will be using the new Bora ULTRA WTO wheels. The Campagnolo Bora ULTRA WTO wheels come in two depths: 45 mm and 60mm. Both employ a 23mm 2-WAY FIT internal rim bed and should fit well with the team’s 28mm or 30mm Continental tubeless tires. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/special-Bora-WTO-Matt-Edition-aero-road-bike-wheels_with-matte-finish-to-match-new-Super-Record-S-gruppo-jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"922\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/special-Bora-WTO-Matt-Edition-aero-road-bike-wheels_with-matte-finish-to-match-new-Super-Record-S-gruppo-1536x922.webp\" alt=\"2025 Campagnolo Bora WTO Matte Edition wheels, up close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/special-Bora-WTO-Matt-Edition-aero-road-bike-wheels_with-matte-finish-to-match-new-Super-Record-S-gruppo-1536x922.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/special-Bora-WTO-Matt-Edition-aero-road-bike-wheels_with-matte-finish-to-match-new-Super-Record-S-gruppo-297x178.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/special-Bora-WTO-Matt-Edition-aero-road-bike-wheels_with-matte-finish-to-match-new-Super-Record-S-gruppo-120x72.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/special-Bora-WTO-Matt-Edition-aero-road-bike-wheels_with-matte-finish-to-match-new-Super-Record-S-gruppo-768x461.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/special-Bora-WTO-Matt-Edition-aero-road-bike-wheels_with-matte-finish-to-match-new-Super-Record-S-gruppo-jpg.webp 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to the  Bora ULTRA WTO, they will use the Bora Ultra WTO TT disc wheel (just 930 grams) for time trials. All Bora ULTRA TWO wheels spin on Campagnolos’ CULT  ceramic bearings. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1707\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Campagnolo Cofidis Shifters and brakes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--scaled.webp 1707w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--1536x2303.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--768x1151.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--1024x1536.webp 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Campagnolo-Cofidis-Shifters-and-brakes--1366x2048.webp 1366w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s Next For Campagnolo? </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ll have to wait and see. They are back on the World Tour and showcasing their beautiful craftsmanship, piloted by the world’s best athletes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.campagnolo.com/us-en/\">Campagnolo.com</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/campagnolo-returns-to-the-world-tour-racing-with-team-cofidis/\">Campagnolo Makes Poetic Return to the World Tour Racing with Team Cofidis</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"80e90b28f7fb7f7a9a1b62652e6517156d90fa8de079ad248aa4b4d121d1c736","category":"Cycling"}